  "pr_number": 220,
  "issue_number": 48,
  "issue_title": "feat: add IntentGate for local routing",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\n- Add `IntentGate` in the agent package. It classifies non-conversational tasks into one of the five Milestone-2 categories: `ExactCommand`, `KnownSkill`, `UnsafeRequest`, `ClarificationNeeded`, or `LocalModelNeeded`.\n- Wire the gate into `DefaultLocalReasoningCore` after the conversational gate. Each decision routes deterministically:\n\n| Decision               | Effect                                                                                |\n| ---------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| `UnsafeRequest`        | Emit `UserMessage` + `PolicyBlocked` + `FinalAnswer`; runner not invoked.             |\n| `ClarificationNeeded`  | Emit `UserMessage` + `AssistantMessage` asking the user to elaborate; runner not invoked. |\n| `ExactCommand`         | Force `LOCAL_ROUTER` provider on this run so small local models cannot hallucinate an alternate tool call. |\n| `KnownSkill`           | Pass through to the configured provider; existing skill allowlist / policy / approval still gate execution. |\n| `LocalModelNeeded`     | Pass through unchanged.                                                               |\n\n- Unsafe-keyword detection mirrors `DefaultActionPolicy.blockedWorkflow`. The gate fails closed against the same payment / secret / destructive-action vocabulary the policy layer already blocks \u2014 defence in depth, not a replacement.\n\nCloses #34.\n\n## Scope\n\n- `app/src/main/java/dev/touchpilot/app/agent/IntentGate.kt` (new) \u2014 `sealed class IntentDecision` with 5 variants, `class IntentGate` with `classify(task, skills): IntentDecision`.\n- `app/src/main/java/dev/touchpilot/app/agent/LocalReasoningCore.kt`\n  - `DefaultLocalReasoningCore` now takes an `intentGate: IntentGate` (default-constructed) and an `availableSkills: () -> List<Skill>` callback.\n  - `run(task)` consults the gate after the conversational gate; routes per the table above.\n- `app/src/main/java/dev/touchpilot/app/MainActivity.kt` \u2014 passes `availableSkills = { skills }` into the core. One-line change.\n- `app/src/test/java/dev/touchpilot/app/agent/IntentGateTest.kt` (new) \u2014 16 cases covering every category, the precedence between them, blank input, skill-title matching, and a regression that unsafe wins over exact command when both could match.\n- `app/src/test/java/dev/touchpilot/app/agent/LocalReasoningCoreTest.kt` \u2014 4 new cases pinning the core's branch behavior for each non-fall-through intent.\n\n## Testing\n\n- [x] `./gradlew assembleDebug`\n- [ ] `./gradlew assembleRelease`\n- [x] `./gradlew testDebugUnitTest` \u2014 61 cases total green: `IntentGateTest` 16/16, `LocalReasoningCoreTest` 12/12 (8 existing + 4 new), `ConversationalGateTest` 14/14, `AgentEventTest` 6/6, `LocalModelApprovalGateTest` 3/3, plus the existing parser/policy/redactor/local-model suites.\n- [x] `./gradlew lintDebug` \u2014 clean.\n- [x] Manual emulator test (`TouchPilot_API_35`):\n  - `Send this payment` \u2192 \"Blocked by intent gate: payments are blocked\" \u2014 no Android action.\n  - `Do the thing I usually do here` \u2192 \"Clarification requested: ambiguous reference 'do the thing'\" \u2014 no Android action.\n  - `Go back` \u2192 routed through local router \u2192 policy gate raises the inline approval card for `press_back` (MEDIUM risk).\n\n## Risk\n\n- [ ] Touches Android control\n- [x] Touches agent/tool execution\n- [x] Touches approvals/security policy\n- [x] Touches local inference/runtime\n- [ ] Touches persisted data/secrets\n- [x] Touches UI\n- [ ] Docs only\n\n## Screenshots / Traces\n\nAll three intent paths back-to-back on the emulator (Send this payment \u2192 blocked; Do the thing I usually do here \u2192 clarification; Go back \u2192 routed via LOCAL_ROUTER, approval card surfaces for `press_back`):\n\n![Intent gate flows](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/RenzoMXD/touchpilot/pr-34-media/docs/pr-34/intent-gate-flows.png)\n\n## Notes\n\n- The gate does not approve any risky action by itself \u2014 it can only refuse (`UnsafeRequest`), ask for clarification, or hand off to a downstream layer that already runs the existing skill allowlist, policy, approval, and logging code.\n- `KnownSkill` currently uses a simple \"skill title appears in the task\" match. The decision is informational today \u2014 we route through the configured provider rather than auto-selecting a skill \u2014 because skill selection is still a user-driven setting. A follow-up could turn this into an \"I'll use the X skill\" assistant tag in the UI.\n- Conversational gate (`Hello`, `help`) still wins over the intent gate, matching the user expectation that greetings never trigger an action timeline.\n- The \"Working on it.\" card is still emitted by the UI optimistically for non-conversational input, then replaced by the action timeline once the core returns. A future UI refactor that consumes the event listener live could drop the loading card for the synchronous unsafe / clarification short-circuits.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-19T14:05:27.000Z",
